    "terms_link": "Terms of Use",
    "help_body": "<h2>How to Play</h2><p>Fill the entire 8×8 board with 11 tiles. Three grey tiles are already placed — arrange the remaining 8 colored tiles to fill every empty cell.</p><h3>Choose a Level</h3><p>Pick a difficulty from the welcome panel — <strong>Easy</strong>, <strong>Medium</strong>, <strong>Hard</strong>, or <strong>Nightmare</strong> — to play puzzles in order of increasing challenge. Or tap <strong>Random Puzzle</strong> for a surprise.</p><h3>Place a Tile</h3><ul><li><strong>Drag &amp; drop</strong> a tile from the piece tray onto the board.</li><li>Or <strong>tap</strong> a tile to select it (highlighted in yellow), then <strong>tap an empty cell</strong> on the board to place it.</li></ul><h3>Scroll Tiles</h3><ul><li>Use the <kbd>◀</kbd> / <kbd>▶</kbd> arrow buttons beside the piece tray to scroll.</li><li>You can also swipe horizontally on the piece tray.</li></ul><h3>Rotate a Tile</h3><ul><li><strong>Tap</strong> an already-selected tile again to rotate it 90°.</li></ul><h3>Remove a Tile</h3><ul><li><strong>Drag</strong> a placed tile off the board to return it to the tray.</li><li>Or <strong>tap</strong> a placed tile on the board to pick it back up.</li></ul><h3>Controls</h3><ul><li><kbd>◀ / ▶</kbd> — navigate between puzzles in a level.</li><li><kbd>Random</kbd> — load a random puzzle.</li><li><kbd>Hint</kbd> — reveal the correct position of one unplaced tile (3 per day).</li></ul><h3>Offline</h3><p>Octile works offline with 88 random puzzles and 22 puzzles per level. Scores sync when you reconnect.</p><h3>Pacing</h3><p>Octile is designed for short, focused play sessions. The puzzles aren't going anywhere—come back whenever you're ready.</p><p>Your first puzzle each day is free. After that, each puzzle costs one play. Plays recover over time — one every two hours, up to five.</p><p><em>Some puzzles need a little distance to become clear.</em></p>",
